Feature: Shopping Cart # features/cart.feature:1
  As a logged-in user I want to add and remove items from the cart.
  Feature: Shopping Cart  # features/cart.feature:1

  Scenario: Add one item to cart             # features/cart.feature:7
    Given I am logged in as "standard_user"  # features/steps/login_steps.py:25
    Given I am on the inventory page         # features/steps/login_steps.py:58
    When I add the first product to the cart # features/steps/cart_steps.py:7
    Then the cart badge should show "1" item # features/steps/cart_steps.py:22
      ASSERT FAILED: Expected cart badge 1, got 0


  Scenario: Remove one item from cart             # features/cart.feature:12
    Given I am logged in as "standard_user"       # features/steps/login_steps.py:25
    Given I am on the inventory page              # features/steps/login_steps.py:58
    And I add the first product to the cart       # None
    And the cart badge should show "1" item       # None
    When I remove the first product from the cart # None
    Then the cart badge should not be visible     # None

  Scenario: Verify cart badge count with multiple items  # features/cart.feature:19
    Given I am logged in as "standard_user"              # features/steps/login_steps.py:25
    Given I am on the inventory page                     # features/steps/login_steps.py:58
    When I add the first product to the cart             # features/steps/cart_steps.py:7
    And I add the second product to the cart             # features/steps/cart_steps.py:12
    Then the cart badge should show "2" items            # features/steps/cart_steps.py:27
      ASSERT FAILED: Expected cart badge 2, got 0


  Scenario: Remove item from cart page        # features/cart.feature:25
    Given I am logged in as "standard_user"   # features/steps/login_steps.py:25
    Given I am on the inventory page          # features/steps/login_steps.py:58
    And I add the first product to the cart   # None
    When I open the cart                      # None
    And I remove the first item from the cart # None
    Then the cart should have "0" items       # None

